Q3) Explain the difference between local and instance variables?

Ans-

--Local variables-
	1.A variable that is typically used in a method or a constructor
	2.Do not have a default values
	3.Local variables create when entering the method or a constructor
	4.Local variables destroy when existing the method or a constructor
	5.Access limited to method in which declared
	
--Instance variables-
	1.A variable that is bounded to the object itself.
	2.Can have default values
	3.Instance variables create when creating an object
	4.Instance variables destroy when destroying the object
	5.Access controlled by public and private
